meta {
  name: Validate – Server-side Path
  type: http
  seq: 3
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/v1/validate?file_path=/app/data/sales.csv
  body: none
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  ## Validate – Server-side Path

  Trigger validation by passing an absolute path to a file that already
  exists on the server (inside the container at `/app/data/`).

  Useful for scheduled pipelines that drop files into the data directory.

  ### Query params
  | Param | Required | Description |
  |-------|----------|-------------|
  | `file_path` | No | Absolute server-side path to a `.csv` or `.parquet` file |

  ### Expected response `200`
  ```json
  {
    "file": "/app/data/sales.csv",
    "total_rows": 10,
    "valid_rows": 10,
    "invalid_rows": 0,
    "is_valid": true,
    "errors": []
  }
  ```

  ### Error responses
  | Status | Cause |
  |--------|-------|
  | 400    | Path points to an unsupported file extension |
  | 404    | File does not exist at the given path |
  | 500    | Internal pipeline failure |
}
